    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are an ATS Resume Screening Assistant.\n\nRead the resume text provided below.\n\nExtract the following information exactly as it appears in the resume:\n- Name\n- Email\n- Phone Number\n- LinkedIn\n- Education\n- Experience\n- Skills\n- Projects\n- Certifications\n\nRequired Skills:\n- Python\n- SQL\n- Machine Learning\n- Data Analysis\n- Power BI\n\nInstructions:\n1. Compare the candidate's skills with the required skills.\n2. List the matching skills in \"skillsFound\".\n3. List the missing required skills in \"missingSkills\".\n4. Calculate a score out of 100.\n5. If the score is 70 or above, set recommendation to \"Selected\".\n6. If the score is below 70, set recommendation to \"Rejected\".\n7. If a field is not available in the resume, return an empty string \"\" or an empty array [].\n8. Return ONLY valid JSON. Do not include explanations, markdown, or extra text.\n\nReturn the result in this format:\n\n{\n  \"name\": \"\",\n  \"email\": \"\",\n  \"phone\": \"\",\n  \"linkedin\": \"\",\n  \"education\": [],\n  \"experience\": [],\n  \"certifications\": [],\n  \"projects\": [],\n  \"skillsFound\": [],\n  \"missingSkills\": [],\n  \"score\": 0,\n  \"recommendation\": \"\"\n}\n\nResume:\n\n{{$json.text}}",
        "batching": {}
      },
      "id": "1feaedcb-12f4-4fc4-93a5-37b26a36e6c9",
      "name": "Basic LLM Chain",
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.chainLlm",
      "typeVersion": 1.9,
      "position": [
